Name: Description
COVID-19 Hospitalizations by Race/Ethnic:
Racial groups are defined such that: 
Asian = Asian or Pacific Islander
Black = Black or African American
Hispanic = Hispanic or Latino, regardless of race
White = White 

Rates are age adjusted according to the U.S. 2000 standard population, per 100,000 people by racial/ethnic group.

Name: Source Notes
COVID-19 Hospitalizations by Race/Ethnic:
New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, COVID-19 Data (2020). Retrieved from: https://github.com/nychealth/coronavirus-data

Data for COVID-19 Hospitalizations were updated weekly for the period of April 2, 2020 through April 2, 2021. These data are no longer being regularly updated. For the latest data on COVID-19, see: https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data.page

Name: Notes
COVID-19 Hospitalizations by Race/Ethnic:
Data on people identified as American Indian/Alaska Native, two or more races, or other races/ethnicities are not shown, as precise race-specific population estimates are not available for these groups in NYC. Race/ethnicity information is most complete for people who have been hospitalized or have died. Data are cumulative and do not represent new cases per day listed. Data are being collected in real-time and are preliminary and subject to change as COVID-19 response continues. Due to delays in reporting, recent data are incomplete. 
Decreases in hospitalization data after 10/6, are due to enhanced data cleaning processes which restricts the classification of hospitalizations due to COVID-19 only if the patient was admitted within 14 days of diagnosis date.
